^b@2^*bQ.^*n   What is a the Analyser ?  

|cp|8|at|^*bA.^*n|cp||at|   When you are  ^*bInside a Deal^*n  and have switched on the ^*bDDS^*n  then in addition to the green and amber ovals you will see a button saying  ^*bAnalyse^*n, meaning analyse  ^*bTHIS DEAL^*n.   Clicking this button will take the existing deal and pass it to the DDS which will then return with a table of who can make what in which contacts.

This table is displayed with 20 entries (4 seats by 5 denominations).  Hovering over any entry will tell you how many can be made by that declarer.  Clicking on a entry will set that as the contract and allow you to play the cards of THAT deal in the new contract.   ^*bOR^*n  by just looking at the ovals you will be able to see the more complex winning lines more easily.


|fp|3|cp|2|at|Hint|fp||at|^*n      Select the ^*bAutoPlay^*n TAB (right column) and switch to both sides auto play.  
Once finished you can use  ^*bReview^*n  to inspect the chosen line (with the DDS ovals showing) and so investigate an optimal line.|cp||at|^*n


^b@2^*bQ.^*n   Some deals appear to take a long time to Analyse ? 

|cp|8|at|^*bA.^*n|cp||at|   Yes  -   a very few, normally especially created deals, can take along time to Analyse, aaBridge will pause until the analysis is complete.   

^*bAdvice:^*n  Don't use the Analyser or even the DDS on such 'created' deals.|

